            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#GC">
                <p>Diodoros Appeiraios, son of Tittelos, dedicates (a statue of) his sister Minyra, (wife?) of Artemon, priestess, to Aphrodite Ourania.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#GC">
                <p>Diodoros Appeiraios, figlio di Tittelos, dedica (una statua della) sorella Minyra, (moglie?) di Artemon, sacerdotessa, a Afrodite Ourania.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>A new text (<ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001700">ISic001700</ref>) found in 2021 in situ records the same Diodoros Appeiraios.<!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--Diodoros Appeiraios, son of Tittelos, in honour of his sister Minyra, ?wife? of Artemon, priestess of Aphrodite Ourania; dedication of a statue. cf. Nenci (1995b: 1183 no.2) which is considered contemporary and even the same person possibly; also Nenci (1991a: 925) for relevant discussion.--></p>
            </div>
